narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I explored the idea of a teenager to a great extent. Doing so taught me a lot of history and things about myself. I learned how to use a variety of sources and draw the important information out of texts. Mainly, I learned how to really flush an idea out.

This course enabled me to critically think about the construction of history and ways in which categories of people change and stagnate. A focus on analyzing primary sources also improved my writing for history.

I learned quite a bit about the history of teens, which is something I knew almost nothing about before taking this course. I improved my writing skills by learning how to incorporate non-traditional primary sources into my papers. This course exposed me to a lot of non-traditional sources, which is something I really enjoyed.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The class introduced an interesting and diverse array of sources from around the world.
I think this course was really strongthe syllabus, the assignments, and the professor were all amazing. I think the course could be improved by having more primary source discussions in class.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. Loved this seminar. A great way to get a writing credit and learn about music, dance, consumer culture, and yourself in a friendly setting.
100% yes. The topic was really fun to learn about, and Miranda is an outstanding teacher.
